This by far has been my favorite place I've been to while visiting Chicago. Stopped in Saturday afternoon and it was kinda empty just a handful of folks there. The atmosphere was welcoming and fun. He just might be the nicest bartender I have ever met. He somehow got me hooked playing this game with the rest of the bar for the next 4 hours. It literally is a kids toy I'm sure of it. It's so fun and everyone was into it. Definitely recommend going there and check the place out. I'll definitely be making this my new home bar as I'm moving here in November. Oh not to mention I also got 2 free cans of redbull from them. It definitely came in handy today with my hangover. Wish I could give them extra stars for that.

My boyfriend and I just had an overall bad experience here. We wanted to escape the busy street and lines going out the door to all the bars on Hubbard friday night, so we figured we would have some drinks at this sports bar to end our night. We get in and decide to grab a beer at the bar, then grab a table to sit at. Not even five minutes in, we're told by a male server that we need to move and sit at the rail because we brought our beer at the bar and that he makes his money on these tables, then walks away. We honestly didn't even know there were servers, otherwise we would've just opened a tab through one of them. Most bars we've been to at 1am in the morning typically don't. So we just excused his rudeness and sat at the rail, which is conveniently in the way of people playing at the pool table, so we sat closer to the edge. We're minding our own business and have our friends meet us up at this bar. We probably were at this bar for a good half hour to 45min when we got yelled and cursed out by a second server! This female was legit going off on us saying we were too close to one of her tables and this is how she makes a f@&!in living! Mind you, the bar was pretty empty for a Friday night. There were plenty of open tables. Even if we were too close to this specific table, there were plenty of other tables she could have sat her customers at. My bf got upset, told her we're f@&!in leaving, and we left. We've never been treated so rude, especially when we were paying customers and were considering on getting a few more rounds with our friends. If this is how this place treats their customers, i wouldn't be surprised if they shut down. But i do have to say that the bouncer/doorman and the GM were extremely awesome. We told them about our experience and they sincerely apologized and tried to have us come back inside. But at that point, we just didn't want to be around those rude servers or give them anymore of our money. The servers definitely need to be retrained on their customer service or find another job.
